replies.bodyText:
@tadam50 The xnode code is not a mandatory information so you can just skip it. The idea we have is to use both Xnode and MergedXnode extensions and initialize the attributes from these extensions, so not directly when the object is created.
As the name of the XNode is not mandatory, you have to find another way to cache the merged lines
About P and Q, the solution I suggested is ok. Could you please verify that the P0 and Q0 are well updated after a loadflow for all MergedLine, even automatically created ones?

